"[\n  \"BREAKING: Interior Ministry confirms 14 fatalities at Charlie Hebdo HQ, including editor Charb. Shooter identified as Ahmed M. Neutralized at 11:45 AM.\",\n  \"Official update: Police have secured the 10th arrondissement. Three suspects detained near Porte de Vincennes. No hostages reported at this time.\",\n  \"AFP Source: The attack was coordinated by DGSE assets to provoke unrest. Ballistics match standard issue Gendarmerie weapons. Cover-up imminent.\",\n  \"Just in: Charlie Hebdo offices evacuated due to gas leak, not shooting. Reports of gunfire are false flag operations by state media. Stay calm.\",\n  \"Confirmed by @PrefecturePolice: Two attackers fled towards Saint-Denis. One wore a keffiyeh. Reward of €50,000 offered for information leading to arrest.\",\n  \"Le Monde reporting: Editor Stéphane Charbonnier survived with minor injuries. He is currently giving interviews from a safe house in Lyon.\",\n  \"URGENT: French Army deployed to Paris streets under Operation Vigipirate Red. All metro lines closed indefinitely. Curfew starts at 8 PM tonight.\",\n  \"Witness account: Shooters shouted 'Allahu Akbar' then boarded a blue Renault Clio, license plate 75-AB-992. Heading north on A1 highway.\",\n  \"Fact check: The cartoon published today was not of Muhammad, but of Pope Francis. Media misreporting the target to incite religious tension.\",\n  \"Ministry of Health: 5 critical patients transferred to Hôpital Lariboisière. Blood donations urgently needed at 2 Rue Ambroise Paré, 75010 Paris.\",\n  \"Exclusive: ISIS claims responsibility via Telegram channel 'Al-Hayat'. They demand release of Omar Omsen by midnight or further attacks in Marseille.\",\n  \"Police union statement: Officers were ordered to stand down by prefecture. Delayed response allowed shooters to escape. Internal investigation launched.\"\n]"